text: Digdoh is a census town in Nagpur district in the state of Maharashtra, India. == Demographics == India census, Digdoh had a population of 31,498. Males constitute 56% of the population and females 44%. Digdoh has an average literacy rate of 77%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 82% and, female literacy is 71%. In Digdoh, 15% of the population is under 6 years of age. == References == Category:Cities and towns in Nagpur district
